  02 Jan 2005; Daniel Drake <dsd@gentoo.org> mgavideo-0.1.0.ebuild:
  Change virtual/kernel to virtual/linux-sources

  13 Aug 2004; Chris White <chriswhite@gentoo.org> +metadata.xml:
  Adding missing metadata.xml.

  01 Jul 2004; Jeremy Huddleston <eradicator@gentoo.org>
  mgavideo-0.1.0.ebuild:
  virtual/glibc -> virtual/libc

  27 Apr 2004; Aron Griffis <agriffis@gentoo.org> mgavideo-0.1.0.ebuild:
  Add inherit eutils

  12 Jul 2003; Chris PeBenito <pebenito@gentoo.org> mgavideo-0.1.0.ebuild,
  files/mgavideo-0.1.0-rmap_fix.patch:
  Add fix so mgavideo can compile on a rmap kernel.

*mgavideo-0.1.0 (08 Jun 2002)
  
  08 Jun 2002; Gabriele Giorgetti <stroke@gentoo.org> mgavideo-0.1.0.ebuild :

  New version. (0.6 was a test version). See bug #3495
 

*mgavideo-0.1.0.6 (1 Feb 2002)

  8 May 2002; Jon Nelson <jnelson@gentoo.org> mgavideo-0.1.0.6.ebuild :
  
  Use check_KV and depend on portage >= 1.9.10

  1 Feb 2002; G.Bevin <gbevin@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :
  
  Added initial ChangeLog which should be updated whenever the package is
  updated in any way. This changelog is targetted to users. This means that the
  comments should well explained and written in clean English. The details about
  writing correct changelogs are explained in the skel.ChangeLog file which you
  can find in the root directory of the portage repository.
